		<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Boston</placeName>&#44; <date>Nov. 6<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1851</date>.</p>
		<p><addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">The Parcel you<lb/> sent me some time ago&#44; I have<lb/> received&#44; and would have written<lb/> to you ere this&#44; had it not been<lb/> for some difficulty that exists between<lb/> <persName>Mr. Strouse</persName> and the Congregation over<lb/> which he officiates&#44; under the circum&#45;<lb/>stances I did not feel justified in<lb/> giving him those books which you<lb/> sent for him&#44; those school Books<lb/> I mean&#44; please let me know&#44; if<lb/> you wish me to give them to him<lb/> and also <sic>wheather</sic> I shall collect<lb/> the money for them.  <persName>Mr. Milkman</persName><lb/> does not want the Prayer Book you<lb/> sent for him&#44; but will take a<lb/> <sic>german</sic> one&#44; please write me the<lb/> price of the german ones&#44; as you did<lb/> not state in your letter what you sold<lb/> them at&#44; as I have sold two or three of<lb/> them&#44; also what I shall do with the<lb/> Book you intended for <persName>Mr Milkman</persName>.</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)">Yours respectfully</p>
          <p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">Henry S. Spier</persName></p>
		<p>Please correct my name on the cover<lb/> of the occident</p>
		<p rend="The following lines are written sideways in the left column">I have also those Back Nos. of the Occident&#44; which<lb/> <persName>Mr. Milkman</persName> refuses to take&#44; subject to your order&#44; he tells<lb/> me he has written to you.</p>
          
        </body>
